# Scope discipline

Do only what the user asked. Do not expand scope on your own.

- Do NOT try to fix issues the user did not ask about (e.g. off-center
  framing, visual quirks, perf) unless they explicitly request it.
- If the user says a value/parameter is "don't worry about it",
  "doesn't matter", "placeholder", or similar, leave it alone. Do not
  tune, "improve", or refactor it.
- Prefer asking a short question over guessing when intent is unclear.
- Pointing at code (a diff/selection) is not implicit permission to
  change it. Wait for an explicit instruction.
